A N A C T
RELATING TO CRIMINAL OFFENSES -- WEAPONS
Introduced By: Senators Bissaillon, Lawson, Tikoian, LaMountain, and DiPalma
Date Introduced: April 04, 2025
Referred To: Senate Judiciary
(Attorney General)
It is enacted by the General Assembly as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 11-47-33 of the General Laws in Chapter 11-47 entitled "Weapons"
2 is hereby amended to read as follows:
3 11-47-33. Possession of firearms by minors.
4 (a) It shall be unlawful within this state for any person under eighteen (18) years of age to
5 possess and use any firearm unless the person is in the presence of a parent or guardian or
6 supervising adult at any regular and recognized camp or rifle range approved by the Rhode Island
7 state police or by the chief of police of the city or town in which the camp or rifle range is located;
8 provided, that this provision shall not apply to minors engaged in lawful hunting activity under the
9 supervision of a parent or guardian or qualified adult, minors participating in Reserve Officer
10 Training Corps programs, ceremonial parade activities, competitive and target shooting,
11 participants in state militia activities and minors participating in a basic firearms education
12 program; provided, further, that a person under eighteen (18) years of age may carry a firearm,
13 unloaded, in a suitable case to and from his or her home and the camp or range and from the camp
14 or range to other camp or range when accompanied by a parent, guardian, or supervising adult.
15 (b) For purposes of this section only, “qualified adult” means any person twenty-one (21)
16 years of age or older and permitted by law to possess and use the firearm.

1 SECTION 2. This act shall take effect upon passage.
